## Project Management

This project uses the `project-manager` skill from the LLM Skills archive. All feature work flows through markdown files in `docs/`:

```
docs/
  INITIAL_PROMPT.md       Source of truth for product intent (never modified)
  features/*.md           Feature specs — scope authority
  features/template.md    Canonical spec template
  plans/*.md              One plan per feature spec
  tasks/active/*.md       One file per in-flight task
  tasks/archive/*.md      Completed tasks
  issues/*.md             Logged failures and blockers
  workflow/SDLC.md        CAP-ID Feature Abbreviation Registry
```

**Primary commands** (run with leading slash in Claude Code):

- `/continue-tasks` — full orchestration loop (picks next todo task → spawns agent → monitors completion → archives)
- `/review-tasks` — read-only status snapshot
- `/update-tasks` — sync active task files that may have completed
- `/init-features` — capture feature specs from INITIAL_PROMPT.md
- `/add-feature` — add a new feature spec after init
- `/analyze-features` — audit specs for template/CAP-ID/plan-coverage gaps
- `/reinit` — recover from inconsistent state

**Working principles** (also enforced in `AGENTS.md`):

- Feature specs are the final authority on scope; only the user may change them
- Plans are orchestrator-owned; worker agents do not edit plan files
- Every implementation change must trace to an active task file in `docs/tasks/active/`
- Completion sentinels (`## Completion` block at the bottom of a task file) are the wire protocol between agents and the orchestrator

**Before opening a PR:**

1. Confirm the change is covered by an archived task file (or that the user explicitly authorized out-of-band work)
2. Reference the relevant CAP-IDs in the PR description (template at `.github/pull_request_template.md`)

